 Merge Conflicts

1.Understanding and Resolving Merge Conflicts

Q.Explain what merge conflicts are and why they occur.
Ans:Merge conflicts occur when changes from different branches cannot be automatically reconciled by the version control system, typically due to simultaneous or overlapping modifications to the same lines of code.

Q.How to resolve merge conflicts.
Ans:To resolve merge conflicts, manually edit the conflicting files to merge changes, remove conflict markers, test the code, then add and commit the resolved files.

Q.Assignment: Create a merge conflict scenario and resolve it.
Ans:Create a merge conflict by having two branches modify the same lines, then resolve it by manually editing the file to integrate both changes, removing conflict markers, and committing the resolved file.
